#EXTM3U
# ============================================================================
#  SabiStream — combined demo playlist  (Live TV + Movies + Series)   v2
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Built for Google Play review / closed testing. Copyright-safe: contains ONLY
#  Creative Commons open movies (Blender Foundation — Big Buck Bunny, CC BY 3.0,
#  peach.blender.org; Sintel, CC BY 3.0, durian.blender.org), a free public
#  bitrate-test clip (Jellyfish, jell.yfish.us), and public developer test
#  streams (Apple, Mux, Amazon CloudFront). No paid TV, no broadcast/cable
#  rebroadcast, no PPV, no sports.
#
#  WHAT CHANGED IN v2: the Movies and Series entries used to point at Google's
#  public sample bucket (commondatastorage.googleapis.com/gtv-videos-bucket).
#  Google has since locked that bucket down — it now returns AccessDenied on
#  many networks, so those .mp4 files silently failed to play while the HLS Live
#  streams (on other hosts) kept working. All on-demand entries now use
#  test-videos.co.uk, which serves small (1-5 MB) *faststart* H.264 clips that
#  begin playing almost instantly. The Live section is unchanged.
#
#  HOW THE THREE TABS GET POPULATED  (SabiStream classifies a plain M3U by the
#  URL + name, NOT by the group name):
#    * Live TV - live HLS streams (.m3u8). group-title -> the Live category.
#    * Movies  - direct video files (.mp4) with no episode tag.
#                group-title -> the Movie category.
#    * Series  - .mp4 files whose NAME carries an episode tag like S01E01.
#                Episodes group by the show title (the text BEFORE the SxxEyy
#                token); the season comes from the Sxx number.
#
#  WHY THE MOVIES BELOW USE .mp4 AND NOT .m3u8: an entry whose GROUP is "Movies"
#  but is served as a live .m3u8 stream is filed under LIVE on purpose, so that
#  a genuine live "Movies 24" TV channel never gets mis-sorted into the Movies
#  tab. On-demand content therefore has to look on-demand (a real file URL, or a
#  /movie//series/ path), which is what a real IPTV panel's M3U export also does.
# ============================================================================


